#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn42.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn42.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 42 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 42 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:0.2"
msgid "1. Gāmaṇivagga "
msgstr "1. Chiefs "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11. Bhadrakasutta → bhadra (or bhagandha-haṭṭhaka) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Bhadrakasutta "
msgstr "11. With Bhadraka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn42.11:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā mallesu viharati uruvelakappaṃ nāma mallānaṃ nigamo. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Mallas, near the Mallian town called Uruvelakappa. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhadrako gāmaṇi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho bhadrako gāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Bhadraka the village chief went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:1.3"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā dukkhassa samudayañca atthaṅgamañca desetū”ti. "
msgstr "“Please, sir, teach me the origin and cessation of suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Ahañce → ahaṃ ca (si, s1, s2, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn42.11:1.4"
msgid "“Ahañce te, gāmaṇi, atītamaddhānaṃ ārabbha dukkhassa samudayañca atthaṅgamañca deseyyaṃ: "
msgstr "“Chief, if I were to teach you about the origin and ending of suffering in the past, saying "

msgctxt "sn42.11:1.5"
msgid "‘evaṃ ahosi atītamaddhānan’ti, tatra te siyā kaṅkhā, siyā vimati. "
msgstr "‘this is how it was in the past,’ you might have doubts or uncertainties about that. "

#. VAR: Ahañce → ahaṃ ca (si, s1, s2, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn42.11:1.6"
msgid "Ahañce te, gāmaṇi, anāgatamaddhānaṃ ārabbha dukkhassa samudayañca atthaṅgamañca deseyyaṃ: "
msgstr "If I were to teach you about the origin and ending of suffering in the future, saying "

msgctxt "sn42.11:1.7"
msgid "‘evaṃ bhavissati anāgatamaddhānan’ti, tatrāpi te siyā kaṅkhā, siyā vimati. "
msgstr "‘this is how it will be in the future,’ you might have doubts or uncertainties about that. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:1.8"
msgid "Api cāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, idheva nisinno ettheva te nisinnassa dukkhassa samudayañca atthaṅgamañca desessāmi. "
msgstr "Rather, chief, I will teach you about the origin and ending of suffering as I am sitting right here and you are sitting right there. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:1.9"
msgid "Taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:1.10"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho bhadrako gāmaṇi bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Bhadraka replied. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:1.11"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.328, sc2
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gāmaṇi, "
msgstr "“What do you think, chief? "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.2"
msgid "atthi te uruvelakappe manussā yesaṃ te vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "Are there any people here in Uruvelakappa who, if they were executed, imprisoned, fined, or condemned, it would cause you sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.3"
msgid "“Atthi me, bhante, uruvelakappe manussā yesaṃ me vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti. "
msgstr "“There are, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.4"
msgid "“Atthi pana te, gāmaṇi, uruvelakappe manussā yesaṃ te vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "“But are there any people here in Uruvelakappa who, if they were executed, imprisoned, fined, or condemned, it would not cause you sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.5"
msgid "“Atthi me, bhante, uruvelakappe manussā yesaṃ me vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti. "
msgstr "“There are, sir.” "

# NOTE: BB notes at the start of the series of questions that BB omits the nagative form by omission. However in MS the omission occurs here.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.6"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, gāmaṇi, hetu, ko paccayo yena te ekaccānaṃ uruvelakappiyānaṃ manussānaṃ vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "“What’s the cause, chief, what’s the reason why, if this was to happen to some people it could cause you sorrow, while if it happens to others it does not?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.7"
msgid "“Yesaṃ me, bhante, uruvelakappiyānaṃ manussānaṃ vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā, atthi me tesu chandarāgo. "
msgstr "“The people regarding whom this would give rise to sorrow are those I desire and love. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.8"
msgid "Yesaṃ pana, bhante, uruvelakappiyānaṃ manussānaṃ vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā, natthi me tesu chandarāgo”ti. "
msgstr "The people regarding whom this would not give rise to sorrow are those I don’t desire and love.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.9"
msgid "“Iminā tvaṃ, gāmaṇi, dhammena diṭṭhena viditena akālikena pattena pariyogāḷhena atītānāgate nayaṃ nehi: "
msgstr "“With this present phenomenon that is seen, known, immediate, attained, and fathomed, you may infer to the past and future: "

#. VAR: uppajji → uppajjati (sabbattha)
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.10"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho kiñci atītamaddhānaṃ dukkhaṃ uppajjamānaṃ uppajji sabbaṃ taṃ chandamūlakaṃ chandanidānaṃ. "
msgstr "‘All the suffering that arose in the past was rooted and sourced in desire. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.11"
msgid "Chando hi mūlaṃ dukkhassa. "
msgstr "For desire is the root of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.12"
msgid "Yampi hi kiñci anāgatamaddhānaṃ dukkhaṃ uppajjamānaṃ uppajjissati, sabbaṃ taṃ chandamūlakaṃ chandanidānaṃ. "
msgstr "All the suffering that will arise in the future will be rooted and sourced in desire. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.13"
msgid "Chando hi mūlaṃ dukkhassā’”ti. "
msgstr "For desire is the root of suffering.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.14"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! "

#. VAR: subhāsitañcidaṃ → subhāsitamidaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.15"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā: "
msgstr "How well said this was by the Buddha! "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.16"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci dukkhaṃ uppajjamānaṃ uppajjati, sabbaṃ taṃ chandamūlakaṃ chandanidānaṃ. "
msgstr "‘All the suffering that arises is rooted and sourced in desire. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.17"
msgid "Chando hi mūlaṃ dukkhassā’ti. "
msgstr "For desire is the root of suffering.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: I couldn’t resist “Oliver” for ciravasi. get it? “O-Live-er” Anyone? Just me, then.
#. VAR: āvasathe → āvesane (?)
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.18"
msgid "Atthi me, bhante, ciravāsī nāma kumāro bahi āvasathe paṭivasati. "
msgstr "I have a boy called Ciravāsi, who resides in a house away from here. "

#. VAR: uyyojemi → uyyojesiṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.19"
msgid "So khvāhaṃ, bhante, kālasseva vuṭṭhāya purisaṃ uyyojemi: "
msgstr "I rise early and send someone, saying: "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.20"
msgid "‘gaccha, bhaṇe, ciravāsiṃ kumāraṃ jānāhī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Go, my man, and check on my boy Ciravāsi.’ "

msgctxt "sn42.11:2.21"
msgid "Yāvakīvañca, bhante, so puriso nāgacchati, tassa me hoteva aññathattaṃ: "
msgstr "Until they get back I worry: "

#. VAR: ābādhayitthā’”ti → ābādhayethāti (s1-3, km, mr) | ābādhayessati (pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.11:2.22"
msgid "‘mā heva ciravāsissa kumārassa kiñci ābādhayitthā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘I hope nothing’s wrong with Ciravāsi!’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn42.11:3.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gāmaṇi, "
msgstr "“What do you think, chief? "

msgctxt "sn42.11:3.2"
msgid "ciravāsissa kumārassa vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "If Ciravāsi was executed, imprisoned, fined, or condemned, would it cause you sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:3.3"
msgid "“Ciravāsissa me, bhante, kumārassa vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā jīvitassapi siyā aññathattaṃ, kiṃ pana me nuppajjissanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti. "
msgstr "“How could it not, sir?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:3.4"
msgid "“Imināpi kho etaṃ, gāmaṇi, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ: "
msgstr "“This too is a way to understand: "

msgctxt "sn42.11:3.5"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci dukkhaṃ uppajjamānaṃ uppajjati, sabbaṃ taṃ chandamūlakaṃ chandanidānaṃ. "
msgstr "‘All the suffering that arises is rooted and sourced in desire. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:3.6"
msgid "Chando hi mūlaṃ dukkhassā’ti. "
msgstr "For desire is the root of suffering.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn42.11:4.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gāmaṇi, "
msgstr "What do you think, chief? "

#. VAR: ciravāsimātā → ciravāsissa mātā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.11:4.2"
msgid "yadā te ciravāsimātā adiṭṭhā ahosi, assutā ahosi, te ciravāsimātuyā chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Before you’d seen or heard of Ciravāsi’s mother, did you have any desire or love or fondness for her?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:4.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:4.4"
msgid "“Dassanaṃ vā te, gāmaṇi, āgamma savanaṃ vā evaṃ te ahosi: "
msgstr "“Then was it because you saw or heard of her that you had "

msgctxt "sn42.11:4.5"
msgid "‘ciravāsimātuyā chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vā’”ti? "
msgstr "desire or love or fondness for her?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:4.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.330, sc5
msgctxt "sn42.11:5.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gāmaṇi, "
msgstr "“What do you think, chief? "

msgctxt "sn42.11:5.2"
msgid "ciravāsimātuyā te vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "If Ciravāsi’s mother was executed, imprisoned, fined, or condemned, would it cause you sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:5.3"
msgid "“Ciravāsimātuyā me, bhante, vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā jīvitassapi siyā aññathattaṃ, kiṃ pana me nuppajjissanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti. "
msgstr "“How could it not, sir?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.11:5.4"
msgid "“Imināpi kho etaṃ, gāmaṇi, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ: "
msgstr "“This too is a way to understand: "

msgctxt "sn42.11:5.5"
msgid "‘yaṃ kiñci dukkhaṃ uppajjamānaṃ uppajjati, sabbaṃ taṃ chandamūlakaṃ chandanidānaṃ. "
msgstr "‘All the suffering that arises is rooted and sourced in desire. "

msgctxt "sn42.11:5.6"
msgid "Chando hi mūlaṃ dukkhassā’”ti. "
msgstr "For desire is the root of suffering.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn42.11:5.7"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

